article.description: Sacramento limited San Antonio to a near-franchise low for field goals attempted, and Yolanda Griffith had 21 points and 10 rebounds to lead the Monarchs to a 71-67 victory over the Silver Stars on Friday.
article.headline: Griffith's 21 and 10 lead Sacramento
article.linkText: Monarchs' stingy defense stifles Silver Stars
article.story:
SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- Sacramento limited San Antonio to a near-franchise low for field goals attempted, and Yolanda Griffith had 21 points and 10 rebounds to lead the Monarchs to a 71-67 victory over the Silver Stars on Friday. The Monarchs held San Antonio to 47 shots from the floor. The franchise low for shots attempted is 43 on July 26, 2001, when the Silver Stars were the Utah Starzz. The Silver Stars, who have lost all three games this season, also tied a franchise record for fewest field goals attempted with 19 for one half. The Silver Stars were able to stay close because of free throws. San Antonio went to the line 31 times, nine more than Sacramento, and sank all but six tries. San Antonio didn't score until 3:16 into the game on Marie Ferdinand's jump shot. Combined with the final 3:22 Tuesday at Detroit, where San Antonio was outscored 16-0, the Silver Stars were outscored 22-0 over a stretch of 6:38. Ferdinand led San Antonio with 17 points, eight rebounds and four assists. Ticha Penicheiro hit all six of her free throws in the final 22 seconds to preserve the victory. San Antonio trailed 25-24 with 3:03 left in the first half, but Sacramento hit its final five shots from the floor to go ahead 36-26 at halftime.< Game notes
Sacramento played its second of four road games to open the season and has won both. ... Chantelle Anderson, dealt by Sacramento to San Antonio on May 18 for a first-round selection in next year's draft, scored three points and grabbed two rebounds in 19 minutes before fouling out against her old team.
